<item>
            <title>[QPID-5224] [Java 0-x Client] connection is abruptly closed when creating consumers against RabbitMQ</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-5224</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the Qpid 0.24 AMQP 0-x JMS client, attempting to create consumers against a RabbitMQ broker results in the connection being abruptly closed. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reported by a user in this thread:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/qpid-dev/201310.mbox/%3C1381164667512-7599126.post%40n2.nabble.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/qpid-dev/201310.mbox/%3C1381164667512-7599126.post%40n2.nabble.com%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Qpid 0.24 AMQP 0-x client, RabbitMQ 2.x / 3.x&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12673627">QPID-5224</key>
            <summary>[Java 0-x Client] connection is abruptly closed when creating consumers against RabbitMQ</summary>
